structures.graph
Class UndirGraph<T>

java.lang.Object
  structures.graph.DirGraph<T>
      structures.graph.UndirGraph<T>

public class UndirGraph<T>
extends DirGraph<T>

This class implements an undirected graph. Since an undirected graph is a special kind of directed graph--an undirected edge is two directed edges in opposite directions--it is implemented by subclassing DirGraph.

Author:
Sesh Venugopal

addEdge

public void addEdge(int vertexNumber,
                    Neighbor nbr)
Description copied from class: DirGraph
Adds an edge from a given vertex (internal number) to another (neighbor). Note: If this vertex already has an edge to this neighbor, this method will return without doing anything. In other words, multiple edges are not supported.

Overrides:

Parameters:
vertexNumber - Internal number of vertex.
